Streaming Insights and Data Actions Limits and Behaviors

Streaming insights and data actions have some limits and enforced behaviors in Data Cloud. Review the limits before creating an insight.

For guidance on limitations, see Data Cloud Limits and Guidelines.

Streaming Insights and Data Actions Limits
FEATURE OR FUNCTION	LIMITS
Total number of streaming insights	20
Total number of measures	5
Total number of dimensions	10
Aggregation time window	
Minimum: 1 minute
Maximum: 24 hours

Join	Inner
Aggregations	

Available for insights created using SQL and the builder:

SUM
AVG
MIN
MAX
COUNT
MEAN
APPROX_COUNT_DISTINCT
LAST
FIRST
PERCENTILE
STDDEV

Join type	
Engagement join individual
Engagement join unified individual profile

Data sources	
Web SDK
Mobile SDK
Marketing Cloud Personalization (formerly Interaction Studio)

Results available via the JDBC API	Yes
Total number of data actions generated per tenant, per minute	100
Total number of data actions per tenant	20
Total number of data action targets per tenant	10
Total number of rules per data action	10
Total number of data attributes per payload	20

When a new data action is created and associated with Salesforce or Webhook, it starts receiving events no later than 15 minutes. This timing also applies to regenerating the signing key.

The core endpoint, where Data Cloud publishes events, has an implicit rate limit of 2,000 calls per hour, per tenant.

Streaming Insights and Data Actions Behaviors
FEATURE OR FUNCTION	BEHAVIOR
Data action target	First-time data action incurs a 15-minute latency in receiving events.
Streaming insights	Only SQL authored streaming insights are currently supported.
Segmentation and activation	Streaming insights aren’t available in segmentation or activation.
Enrichment	Only engagement data participates in streaming insights. Streaming profile data isn’t reconciled in real time.
Data actions	Delivery semantics—at least one time.
Signature key generation	New webhook signature key generation incurs a 15-minute latency in receiving the events.
